# Demonstrates: C98 — vacuous guards provably true from field constraints

# This file covers both lower-bound and positive-constraint tautologies.

precept VacuousGuardsDemo

field Score as number default 50 min 0 max 100
field Rate as number default 5 positive

state Review initial
state Approved
state Escalated

event Submit
event Escalate

# C98: Score is always >= 0 because the field has min 0.
# EXPECT: C98 | severity=warning | match=exact | message=Guard 'when Score >= 0' is provably always true — the condition has no effect. | line=19 | start=27 | end=37
from Review on Submit when Score >= 0 -> transition Approved
from Review on Submit -> transition Approved

# C98: Rate is always > 0 because the field is positive.
# EXPECT: C98 | severity=warning | match=exact | message=Guard 'when Rate > 0' is provably always true — the condition has no effect. | line=24 | start=29 | end=37
from Review on Escalate when Rate > 0 -> transition Escalated
from Review on Escalate -> transition Escalated
